At the request of the second child at home, Runo came to the Seoul Museum. Truthful adventure: the scale of the venue and the attitude of the service staff cannot be praised. Chinese friends support South Korea tourism, and I feel that Korean people should be more professional and enthusiastic, but I feel very embarrassed in the football stadium!

Since you live next to the Seoul Post Building, you must come and see it. The stamps for the Pingchang Winter Olympic Games were issued with three commemorative stamps for the first day. So he took out his notebook and left the three stamps on it. By the way, he covered the stamps of some other sports events. The museum is rich in furnishings and is very visible. There are also exhibition boards for stamps issued over the years, which can be enjoyed. Postal boxes and postal vehicles all over the world are very interesting. For other information, please refer to the Chinese version of the manual.

The Korean Stamp Museum, located at the main post office in Seoul, is an interesting interactive museum. It is not only full of historical information, but also an interactive and interesting place, especially for children. There are wooden paper-cut and jigsaw puzzle games to stimulate your imagination. Postcards can be bought at the small gift counter.
Many traditional Korean stamps can be seen here, which are more commemorative.
If you like stamp collecting, you can have a look. Many collection-grade stamps are very good. There are also some star stamps.

China Stamp Museum is a professional museum of social history. Located at the Peace Gate in Xuanwu District. Established in July 1985. A stamp identification office was established in 1994. There are hundreds of thousands of Chinese and foreign stamps, more than 100 million.
